  "title": "Disagreements among cohabiting and married couples in 22 European countries",
  "abstract": "Cross-national research suggests that married people have higher levels of well-being than cohabiting people. However, relationship quality has both positive and negative dimensions. Researchers have paid little attention to disagreements within cohabiting",
